~/bin
=====

various shellscripts and programs

bar
---

script wrapper that launches lemonbar, sources ~/etc/bar.conf for preconfigured
options. allows changing options through environment variables:

	# geometry options
	W	bar width
	H	bar height
	X	bar x position
	Y	bar y position
	BW	border width
	
	# color options
	BG	background color (hex #[aa]rrggbb)
	FG	foreground color
	BC	border color
	BOT	place bar on bottom (yes/no)
	
	# example:
	(echo "hello!"; sleep 2) | \
	W=200 H=40 X=20 Y=20 BG=\#000000 FG=\#ffeeee BOT=yes bar

colors
------

prints pretty colors.

	usage: colors [-vhs] char
		-v	vertical mode
		-h	horizontal mode
		-s	short mode (default)
		char	char to color & print

compon
------

toggle compton/picom

gettags
-------

python script to print audio ID3/metadata tags

getxres
-------

gets a value for the given Xresource

hilight + lowlight
------------------

set wallpaper/brightness (hilight = high brightness, lowlight = low brightness)

iphex
-----

convert an IP address into hex form (converts each octet into hex,
then concatenates). for example:

	iphex 192.168.0.1
	0xC0A80001

netstop
-------

stop specified network interface (kill dhclient & down the interface).

notif + notified
----------------

notification client + daemon. `notified` is a daemon that listens on the
preconfigured FIFO for text to show in a notification. `notify` is essentially
wrapping echoing text to a FIFO.
example usage:

	notified &
	notif "hello!"

power
-----

xmenu power menu script (shutdown, reboot, sleep, hiberate).

printpdf
-------

print a pdf file.

rec
---

screen recording via ffmpeg w/ notifications.

shot
----

screenshot script w/ notifications.

stacks
------

modular bar launcher. runs a function and pipes it to lemonbar specified
by the first argument. for example:

	# launches the clock bar
	stacks clock &
	# launches wttr module
	stacks wttr &

tmpfox
------

temporary firefox script.
creates a new profile under /tmp, adds options to user.js and  removes profile
after exit/sigint.

wls
---

list window titles + window IDs.
depends: wmutils

xeph
----

Xephyr(1) wrapper.

ytdl + vdl
----------

scripts to download youtube audio/video (audio = ytdl, video = vdl).

